SIMPLE: intorsion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intorsion
<hw>In*tor"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intortio</ets> a curling, crisping: cf. F. <ets>intorsion</ets>.
See <er>Intort</er>, and cf. <er>Intortion</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A winding, bending, or twisting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The bending or twining of any part
of a plant toward one side or the other, or in any direction from the
vertical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intort</ent>⟦br⟧
